race.comment: TEYLU (1) peaks today and has threatened in his last three starts, all at Canberra in stronger. He's fast and will skip over from the awkward gate. He placed his only run here over 1000m, and four winners have come out of that. Has the in-form Boudvillain aboard and is suited. REASONABLE POINT (2) resumes and has trialled well. She has raced well in town and two back was narrowly beaten over this trip at Cranbourne. She should enjoy the run of the race, and Heywood's booking suggests she's pleasing. MISS SCOOP (3) resumed with a nose defeat at Nowra in 66, stalking the lead. Maps well and will be suited around here. Has a talented apprentice in the saddle, and she has more to offer. SANTOLINI (4) was plain at Albury last time, but she impressed winning a CL1 there from the back prior. Gets in well with the 2kg claim and should be hitting the line.
